---
// Problem section — pain point copy + 3 cards
---

<section class="relative z-10 py-24 md:py-32 overflow-hidden">
  <!-- Atmospheric background image -->
  <div class="absolute inset-0 z-0">
    <img
      src="/assets/images/sections/problem-servers.jpg"
      alt=""
      aria-hidden="true"
      class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-[0.12]"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <!-- Heavy dark overlay — text readability first -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#050505] via-[#050505]/70 to-[#050505]"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">

    <!-- Section Label -->
    <p class="section-label text-center slide-fade">The Problem</p>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <h2 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold text-center mb-10 tracking-tight heading-glow slide-scale" data-duration="1.1">
      <span class="heading-gradient">Your Smart Home Has a Landlord.</span>
    </h2>

    <!-- Body Copy -->
    <div class="space-y-6 text-base md:text-lg text-gray-400 font-light leading-relaxed text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16 slide-fade" data-delay="200">
      <p>
        Every time you say "Hey Alexa," your voice travels to a data center, gets processed
        by a corporation, and comes back — if the internet is working. Your routines, your
        habits, your conversations: stored on servers you don't control.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cloud-dependent systems fail when the internet goes down. They slow down during peak
        hours. They get discontinued when the company pivots. And they harvest your data to
        sell you things.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">
        There's a better way. What if your home was intelligent on its own?
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Pain Point Cards -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

      <!-- Card 1: Cloud Dependent -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6 text-center slide-rotate">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-amber-400/[0.08] mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-400/60" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M2 15a5 5 0 015-5 5 5 0 019.9-1A5 5 0 0122 15H2z"/>
            <path d="M8 19l8-8M8 15l4-4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Cloud Dependent</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
          When AWS goes down, so does your home. 7 major outages in 2025 alone.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 2: Always Watching -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6 text-center slide-rotate">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-amber-400/[0.08] mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-400/60" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M1 12s4-8 11-8 11 8 11 8-4 8-11 8S1 12 1 12z"/>
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Always Watching</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
          Voice assistants send recordings to corporate servers. Your home shouldn't be surveillance.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Card 3: Subscription Creep -->
      <div class="glass-card p-6 text-center slide-rotate">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-amber-400/[0.08] mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-amber-400/60" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M12 2v20M17 5H9.5a3.5 3.5 0 000 7h5a3.5 3.5 0 010 7H6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-[var(--font-display)] text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Subscription Creep</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed">
          $10/month here, $15/month there. Your smart home shouldn't have a monthly bill.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
